channel.description: This file is an XML representation of an issue

item.title: [HADOOP-15223] Replace Collections.EMPTY* with empty* when available
item.description: The use of Collections.EMPTY_SET and Collections.EMPTY_MAP often causes unchecked assignment and it should be replaced with Collections.emptySet() and Collections.emptyMap().
item.summary: Replace Collections.EMPTY* with empty* when available

status.description: A resolution has been taken, and it is awaiting verification by reporter. From here issues are either reopened, or are closed.

comments.comment:
For example, in the following code, Collections.EMPTY_SET can be replaced with Collections.emptySet() to avoid unchecked assignment warning.

public Set<String> getAllocationTags() {
  return Collections.EMPTY_SET;
}
Thanks ajisakaa  for reporting this.I will attach a patch later.

+1 overall

Thanks zhenyi for the patch! Some comments:
1. Would you remove existing @SuppressWarning("unchecked") annotations if the annotation is unnecessary? For example, the following annotation is unnecessary after the change.

    @SuppressWarnings("unchecked")
    public Map<String, String> getAttributes() {
      return (attributes == null) ? Collections.emptyMap() : attributes;
    }

2. There are some remaining Collections.EMPTY_MAP and Collections.EMPTY_SET. Would you replace them?
3. I noticed Collections.EMPTY_LIST can be replaced with Collections.emptyList() as well. Would you replace them?

Thanks ajisakaa for comments.I have remove all of Collections.EMPTY_MAP,Collections.EMPTY_SET , Collections.emptyList() and unnecessary @SuppressWarning("unchecked") annotations.Hope you can review again, thanks a lot.
